"AT PLAN & ARKITEKTUR AS has been approved for temporary use of parts of the building in Troms\u00f8. The remaining work includes completion of various floors and facade work, with a deadline of July 1, 2025 for completion. The decision was made based on the Building and Planning Act, and a final inspection and permit are required. The municipality will conduct inspections and fees will be charged for the process.Kommunen har godkjent en s\u00f8knad fra AT PLAN & ARKITEKTUR AS om unntak fra TEK17 for krav til energieffektivitet for et byggeprosjekt i Troms\u00f8. S\u00f8keren har begrunnet at tiltaket vil forbedre energieffektiviteten i bygningen, selv om den ikke oppfyller alle kravene i TEK17. Kommunen vurderer at unntaket er forsvarlig og gir tillatelse. Det er ogs\u00e5 informasjon om klagefrist og gebyrer i dokumentet.The email is regarding additional information requested by the municipality in relation to a deviation application from building regulations. The building elements mostly meet the minimum requirements for thermal insulation, with exceptions identified and addressed. The building has been renovated to improve energy efficiency, including the installation of a heat pump and connection to district heating. An initial energy assessment indicates a significant improvement in energy efficiency. An energy certificate will be issued upon completion of the project.S\u00f8knaden om tillatelse i ett trinn etter plan- og bygningsloven gjelder innvendige arbeider p\u00e5 tre ulike eiendommer i Troms\u00f8. Tiltaket er en bruksendring til kontor og servering- og bevertningssted, samt endring av bygg og riving av deler av bygget. Saken oppfyller ikke kravene for 3 ukers saksbehandling.\n\nThe document provides information about a building project, including the type of measures and use, details about the parties involved, notification status, compliance with regulations, and attachments of plans and declarations. It also includes information on access to water supply, sewage, and drainage systems, as well as responsibility declarations and attachments.This document is a preliminary response to an application for deviation from building regulations for a renovation project in Troms\u00f8. The municipality requires additional information regarding energy efficiency and structural improvements to consider the request. The applicant is asked to provide the necessary details by a specified deadline, and failure to do so may result in the application being rejected. A fee will be charged for incomplete applications. The letter is signed by Bettina Elise Haug, a legal representative from the Urban Development Department.Det er gitt tillatelse til bruksendring og innvendig ombygging av eiendommene Fredrik Langes gate 24, 26, 28 og Gr\u00f8nnegata 72, 74, 76 i Troms\u00f8. Tillatelsen er gitt til AT PLAN & ARKITEKTUR AS, p\u00e5 vegne av SENTRUMSG\u00c5RDEN TROMS\u00d8 AS. Det er vurdert at tiltaket oppfyller kravene til visuelle kvaliteter og p\u00e5virker ikke naturmangfoldet i stor grad. Klagefristen er tre uker, og det er oppgitt informasjon om klageprosessen, samt gebyr for saksbehandling.Summary: The document is a response to a application for consent regarding changes and renovations to a building in Troms\u00f8, Norway. The application includes changes to the building structure, technical installations, fire separation, sound isolation, and wet rooms. The building will primarily be used as office space over four floors, with a restaurant on the first floor and staff facilities in the basement. The total area of the building is 2900 m2 and will accommodate 80 employees. Consent has been granted with conditions.\n\n5 out of 7-8 premises have known tenants, including Arctic Nightlife AS, Spesialistlege AS, Troms\u00f8 Skot\u00f8imagasin AS, Advokatkontoret Finn AS, and Tromstrygd. Documentation provided includes various forms, floor plans, facades, and confirmations of participation in the application process. Known tenants include Arctic Nightlife AS, Spesialistlege AS, Troms\u00f8 Skot\u00f8imagasin AS, Advokatkontoret Finn AS, and Tromstrygd.\n\nThe application consists of a declaration stating that certain safety measures are in place at the workplace in accordance with regulations. The application also includes facilities such as gender-specific showers and toilets for employees, as well as areas for cleaning equipment and break rooms. The Labor Inspection Authority has approved the plans with conditions outlined in the decision, based on relevant legal provisions.\n\nTiltakshavere m\u00e5 sikre at samtykkevilk\u00e5rene blir oppfylt i samsvar med arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven og arbeidsplassforskriften. Arbeidstilsynet kan gjennomf\u00f8re tilsyn for \u00e5 kontrollere oppfyllelsen av vilk\u00e5rene. Samtykket er ikke en generell godkjenning av arbeidsmilj\u00f8et, og det er tiltakshaverens ansvar \u00e5 sikre at kravene overholdes. Etter \u00e5 ha vurdert dokumentasjonen, har Arbeidstilsynet identifisert mangler knyttet til ventilasjon, dagslys og vold/trusler om vold, og vilk\u00e5rene for samtykket er derfor ikke oppfylt. Mer informasjon om kravene finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynets nettside.\n\nTiltakshaver m\u00e5 s\u00f8rge for at ventilasjonsl\u00f8sningene sikrer tilfredsstillende inneklima og ventilasjon. Kravene til ventilasjon er regulert i arbeidsmilj\u00f8loven og arbeidsplassforskriften. Arbeidstilsynet har veiledninger som fastsetter normer for tilfredsstillende inneklima og luftkvalitet, og balansert mekanisk ventilasjon anbefales som en generell l\u00f8sning for tilfredsstillende inneklima.\n\nArbeidstilsynet stiller ikke konkrete krav til ventilasjonsl\u00f8sninger, men til dokumentasjon som viser planlegging av l\u00f8sninger som gir tilfredsstillende inneklima uavhengig av arbeidets art. Kravene til inneklima og luftkvalitet kan normalt oppfylles ved \u00e5 velge ventilasjonsl\u00f8sninger som oppfyller normene. Dokumentasjonskrav og lenker til regelverket finnes p\u00e5 Arbeidstilsynets nettside. Detaljprosjekteringen av ventilasjon er under arbeid, og luftmengdeberegninger per rom m\u00e5 ettersendes n\u00e5r den er ferdigstilt.\n\nArbeidstilsynet har sendt en referanse (236451/2023) til tiltakshaveren ang\u00e5ende krav til dagslys, utsyn, oppdaterte planer, og beskyttelse mot vold og trusler om vold i arbeidslokaler. Det kreves dokumentasjon og oppdateringer i henhold til lover og regler. Tiltakshaveren m\u00e5 ogs\u00e5 betale et gebyr for Arbeidstilsynets saksbehandling og har rett til \u00e5 klage p\u00e5 vedtaket innen tre uker. Informasjonen m\u00e5 deles med arbeidsmilj\u00f8utvalget, verneombudet eller ansattes representant.Application for temporary use permit under Pbl \u00a7 21-10, SAK10 \u00a7 8-1 for various properties in Troms\u00f8. The application is for parts of the roof of the buildings, with remaining minor works to be completed before final approval. The applicant is AT Plan & Arkitektur AS, and contact details are provided for further communication. The application includes attached plans and confirmation of safety measures.The document is a project implementation plan that includes information about the responsible parties, their roles, and planned actions for a construction project in Troms\u00f8. It includes details about design responsibilities, installation work, and control measures for fire safety, sound, ventilation, and other aspects. It also lists the companies involved, their organization numbers, and planned completion dates for their tasks. The document has been electronically signed and archived in Altinn.The document discusses a building permit for a change in use and interior renovation of several properties in Troms\u00f8. The permit was granted by the Building Department, with conditions and requirements outlined. The decision can be appealed, and there is information on the process for complaints. The document also addresses environmental considerations and regulations related to construction activities. A fee is charged for the processing of the permit application.Berit Ballari from AT arkitektur has sent an email to Postmottak Troms\u00f8 kommune regarding a follow-up submission for a one-step application for interior work at Gr\u00f8nnegata 72-76. The original submission was sent on September 1, 2023, but has not been registered in the municipal system. The email includes attachments of approval from the Labor Inspection Authority, revised drawings, and a receipt for the initial application. They have also been granted dispensation for a change of use in the ground floor of Sentrumsg\u00e5rden. The submission is now complete and can be processed within the deadline for one-step applications."